div.div: First, the program moves to the next seat. It then checks if it has gone off the end of the row, if not, you can safely check another seat. If yes, go to first seat of next row. Now, check if you have gone off the end of the plane, if so, go to Restart Booking Logic. If not, you can safely check the first seat in the next row.

div.div: First, check if the seat is already booked. If yes, go to Next Seat Logic. If no, set the seat to booked, note that you have booked another seat, add this seat's seat code to the list, then check if you have booked enough seats for all the passengers stated by the user. If yes, print a representation of the plane. If no, go to Next Seat Logic.

div.div: First, ask the user how many passengers are in the booking, store this result in numOfPassengers. Then, ask what is thier location preference; front, middle or back of the plane. Store this in the variable locationInput. Note down the number of rows in the plane. The collection of three decision blocks uses the user's preference to set the start location for seaching for a free seat in the plane. Once decided, the program moves onto Pre Seat Booking Logic. If the program cannot decide, the user is told the format of the input and asked for their preference again.
